cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SE 

This paper discusses data quality issues and their impact on data mining and machine learning results. It specifically focuses on the effects of missing, inconsistent, and conflicting data on classification, clustering, and regression algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (databases), followed by cs.AI (artificial intelligence) and cs.LG (machine learning). The paper also discusses the impact of dirty data on information retrieval (cs.IR) and software engineering (cs.SE), which makes these two sub-categories also likely.
